Class BBDUnitTestCase<R extends IBBDRow<IBBDField>,L extends BBDRowArrayList<R>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • bbd.BBDUnitTestCase<R,L>
  • Type Parameters:
    R -
    L - 

    public abstract class BBDUnitTestCase<R extends IBBDRow<IBBDField>,L extends BBDRowArrayList<R>>
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstrate test case used with JUnit 4.0 annotations. By extending this class, unit test pojo's get automatic recording of test metrics into the BBD.APIUnitTest table. Extend this for Application level Unit tests for Broker Database level unit tests for each possible API call

        public void addSelectedRows(int selectedRows)
        The test call this method to add some more rows selected to the counter. Using this ADDitive approach, as opposed setSelectedRows(count), one test method could have several select operations and could accumulate a total number of selected rows for the entire test method.
        Parameters:
        selectedRows - count of row selected

      • setTestMethod

        public void setTestMethod()
        Call this for test methods that perform no database operations. If this is not call for this type of test method, no record of the test running will go into the database. Tests that call addSelectedRows, addInsertedRows, addUpdateRows, or addDeleteRows() will have this test method name set automatically and those tests will be recorded in the database.
